---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { siteFromHost, pageTitle, description } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '/use-cases/black-friday';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'use-cases/black-friday');
const desc = description(site, 'use-cases/black-friday');
const heroSubtitle = 'Black Friday is peak stack collision week — Privy pause rules, Sequenzy VIP early access sequencing, Klaviyo sunset unengaged, Postscript frequency caps, and a published collision calendar prevent three offers Tuesday afternoon from burning the list before Cyber Monday.';
const useCaseName = 'Black Friday campaigns';
const trigger = 'Seasonal calendar; VIP early access; teaser sequence';
const timing = 'Teaser week -1; VIP access -24h; general launch; last chance +48h; exclude recent full-price buyers';
const tldrPicks = [
    { label: 'Governance', tool: 'Collision calendar', reason: 'Every layer row for peak week' },
    { label: 'Lifecycle', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'VIP early access and teaser sequences' },
    { label: 'Scale', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Segment sends and deliverability at volume' },
    { label: 'Capture', tool: 'Privy', reason: 'Pause non-essential popups during VIP access' },
];
const faqs = [
  { question: 'How many BFCM emails?', answer: 'Calendar-driven waves — not daily blasts 14 days. Quality segments over volume.' },
  { question: 'VIP early access required?', answer: 'Yes for margin — loyalists first, not deepest discount to everyone.' },
  { question: 'Sunset before BFCM?', answer: '30–90 day unengaged sunset 4–6 weeks before peak.' },
  { question: 'Pause winback?', answer: 'Yes peak week — conflicting offers and list fatigue.' },
  { question: 'SMS BFCM rules?', answer: '72h cap, quiet hours, no email+SMS same discount hour.' },
  { question: 'Recent purchaser exclusion?', answer: '7–14 days full-price buyers excluded from sitewide.' },
  { question: 'Deliverability prep?', answer: 'Auth check, avoid cold volume spike, post-peak audit.' },
  { question: 'Privy during BFCM?', answer: 'Pause non-essential capture — focus sends not popups.' },
  { question: 'Metrics?', answer: 'Revenue per send, daily unsub, margin, Jan reactivation.' },
  { question: 'Replenishment during BFCM?', answer: 'Pause or merge into BFCM calendar — no collision.' },
  { question: 'When freeze changes?', answer: 'Segment logic frozen 1 week before; experiments paused 2 weeks.' },
  { question: 'Biggest BFCM mistake?', answer: 'No collision calendar — stack layers independently discount same shoppers daily.' },
];
const toolReviews = [
    {
      slug: 'klaviyo',
      rank: 1,
      paragraphs: [
      'Klaviyo scale and deliverability monitoring peak week.',
      'Segmented sends over batch blast.',
      'Post-BFCM engagement reporting.',
      ],
    },
    {
      slug: 'sequenzy',
      rank: 2,
      paragraphs: [
      'Sequenzy timed teaser and VIP waves.',
      'Governance-friendly sequence structure.',
      'Pause experiments pre-peak.',
      ],
    },
    {
      slug: 'privy',
      rank: 3,
      paragraphs: [
      'Privy popup pause during VIP window.',
      'Avoid new capture conflicting with sends.',
      'Resume post-peak.',
      ],
    },
    {
      slug: 'omnisend',
      rank: 4,
      paragraphs: [
      'Omnisend multichannel BFCM for SMB.',
      'Monitor SMS costs peak week.',
      'Segment discipline still required.',
      ],
    },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="link text-sm">← Use-case playbooks</a>
      <span class="badge mt-6">Marketing stack playbook</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Shopify marketing stack for {useCaseName}</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">{heroSubtitle}</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-300">Trigger: {trigger} · Timing: {timing}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title={`Stack picks for ${useCaseName}`} picks={tldrPicks} />
    <article class="prose-shopify mb-12 card">
      <h2>Stack execution playbook</h2>
  <p>Black Friday on a six-layer stack is a governance stress test — not a creative contest. Teaser week -1, VIP access -24h, general launch, last chance +48h, each row in collision calendar names owner, segment, max discount, and suppressions. Without calendar, popup + cart + SMS + loyalty + winback collide daily.</p>
  <p>Sunset unengaged 30–90 days before peak — Gmail/Yahoo engagement requirements make BFCM the wrong time to email cold profiles. List hygiene playbook precedes BFCM creative.</p>
  <p>VIP early access before general blast — full-price loyalists and high RFM get first access, not deepest discount. Protect margin on best customers.</p>
  <p>Exclude recent full-price purchasers 7–14 days from sitewide promo — insulting and margin-destructive.</p>
  <p>Pause winback and non-essential experiments 2 weeks before peak. Freeze segment logic changes 1 week before.</p>
  <p>Deliverability: warm domain if new, avoid sudden 10x volume spike without prep, plain-text ratio on heavy promo sends, post-BFCM deliverability audit within 14 days.</p>
  <p>Privy: pause aggressive new capture popups during VIP window — focus on list monetization not list growth peak week.</p>
  <p>Postscript: one SMS per 72h cap, quiet hours, no parallel email+SMS same discount hour one.</p>
  <p>Marsello: if double-points runs, no competing 30% email same day.</p>
  <p>Analytics: revenue per send during BFCM, unsubscribe spike daily, January reactivation rate, margin after discounts — not gross revenue heroics.</p>

      <h2>Merchant scenarios</h2>
  <p><strong>Fashion DTC:</strong> VIP drop access -24h → general BFCM → cart caps → SMS 72h cap → post-peak winback hold.</p>
  <p><strong>Consumable replenishment:</strong> Pause replenishment promos peak week → BFCM only if margin-positive → resume replenishment Dec 5.</p>
  <p><strong>High-AOV restraint:</strong> Financing + VIP early access → max 15% sitewide → no cart escalation peak week.</p>

      <h2>Stack checklist</h2>
      <ul>
    <li>Collision calendar published 6 weeks out</li>
    <li>Unengaged sunset completed</li>
    <li>VIP early access segment defined</li>
    <li>Recent purchaser exclusions live</li>
    <li>Winback paused peak week</li>
    <li>Segment logic frozen 1 week before</li>
    <li>SMS frequency cap 72h</li>
    <li>Privy popup pause rules documented</li>
    <li>Deliverability auth verified</li>
    <li>Daily unsubscribe monitoring</li>
    <li>Post-BFCM deliverability audit scheduled</li>
    <li>Margin after discount tracked daily</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Exclusions (non-negotiable)</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Recent purchasers at full price</li>
    <li>Unengaged contacts (sunset first)</li>
    <li>Customers in active winback with better offer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Metrics that prove quality</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Revenue per send during BFCM</li>
    <li>Unsubscribe spike</li>
    <li>Deliverability post-BFCM</li>
    <li>January reactivation rate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Common mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Daily blasts for 2 weeks straight</li>
    <li>No VIP early access</li>
    <li>Ignoring post-BFCM deliverability damage</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>BFCM stack governance map</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>Calendar: Shared doc</h3>
    <p>Every layer every day peak week.</p>
    <p>Owner + max discount + suppressions per row.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Three offers Tuesday afternoon.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Zero undocumented collisions peak week.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Lifecycle: Sequenzy</h3>
    <p>Teaser, VIP, general, last chance sequences.</p>
    <p>Timed waves not simultaneous blast.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Daily blasts 14 days straight.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Revenue per send not declining day 3+.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>List hygiene: Klaviyo</h3>
    <p>Sunset unengaged pre-peak.</p>
    <p>Engaged-only peak volume.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Cold profiles emailed BFCM — spam risk.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Sunset completed 30 days pre.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>SMS: Postscript</h3>
    <p>Capped urgency not parallel blast.</p>
    <p>72h cap per subscriber.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> SMS opt-out spike &gt;2%.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Daily SMS opt-out rate.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Analytics: Shopify</h3>
    <p>Margin, unsub, Jan reactivation.</p>
    <p>Post-peak retrospective.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Gross revenue without list health.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> January revenue vs prior year.</p>
  </div>

      <h2>Timing and trigger governance</h2>
  <p>Teaser: week -1.</p>
  <p>VIP: -24h general.</p>
  <p>General launch: BFCM day.</p>
  <p>Last chance: +48h.</p>
  <p>Resume normal flows: +7 days post-peak.</p>

      <h2>Measurement across the stack</h2>
  <p>Revenue per send peak week.</p>
  <p>Daily unsubscribe rate.</p>
  <p>Deliverability post-peak.</p>
  <p>January reactivation.</p>
  <p>Margin after all BFCM discounts.</p>

      <h2>Related playbooks</h2>
  <p>Guide: <a class="link" href="/guides/seasonal-campaigns">seasonal governance</a>.</p>
  <p>Hygiene: <a class="link" href="/guides/list-hygiene">list hygiene</a>.</p>
  <p>Discount: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount strategy</a>.</p>

<h2>Stack coordination for Black Friday campaigns</h2>
<p>Black Friday campaigns is not an email template problem — it is a stack handoff problem. Trigger: Seasonal calendar; VIP early access; teaser sequence Timing: Teaser week -1; VIP access -24h; general launch; last chance +48h; exclude recent full-price buyers Every layer must read the same customer state: capture tags from Privy, lifecycle execution in Sequenzy, proof modules from Yotpo, loyalty tier from Marsello, SMS consent from Postscript. When prepare high-volume campaigns without burning the list, margin after discount matters more than attributed revenue.</p>
<p><strong>Calendar:</strong> Every layer every day peak week. Playbook fit: Owner + max discount + suppressions per row. Failure mode: Three offers Tuesday afternoon. Operator test: Zero undocumented collisions peak week.</p>
<p><strong>Lifecycle:</strong> Teaser, VIP, general, last chance sequences. Playbook fit: Timed waves not simultaneous blast. Failure mode: Daily blasts 14 days straight. Operator test: Revenue per send not declining day 3+.</p>
<p><strong>List hygiene:</strong> Sunset unengaged pre-peak. Playbook fit: Engaged-only peak volume. Failure mode: Cold profiles emailed BFCM — spam risk. Operator test: Sunset completed 30 days pre.</p>
<p><strong>SMS:</strong> Capped urgency not parallel blast. Playbook fit: 72h cap per subscriber. Failure mode: SMS opt-out spike &gt;2%. Operator test: Daily SMS opt-out rate.</p>
<p><strong>Analytics:</strong> Margin, unsub, Jan reactivation. Playbook fit: Post-peak retrospective. Failure mode: Gross revenue without list health. Operator test: January revenue vs prior year.</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Fashion DTC:</strong> VIP drop access -24h → general BFCM → cart caps → SMS 72h cap → post-peak winback hold. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Consumable replenishment:</strong> Pause replenishment promos peak week → BFCM only if margin-positive → resume replenishment Dec 5. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — High-AOV restraint:</strong> Financing + VIP early access → max 15% sitewide → no cart escalation peak week. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<h2>Checklist execution notes</h2>
<p>Collision calendar published 6 weeks out — assign a named owner and add to collision calendar if the checklist item touches offers across capture, email, SMS, or loyalty.</p>
<p>Unengaged sunset completed — assign a named owner and add to collision calendar if the checklist item touches offers across capture, email, SMS, or loyalty.</p>
